SIMPLE: betimes
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Betimes
<hw>Be*times"</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>be-</ets> (for
<ets>by</ets>) + <ets>time</ets>; that is, by the proper time. The
<ets>-s</ets> is an adverbial ending.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In good
season or time; before it is late; seasonably; early.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To measure life learn thou <qex>betimes</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To rise <qex>betimes</qex> is often harder than to do all the
day's work.</q> <rj><qau>Barrow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In a short time; soon; speedily; forth
with.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He tires <qex>betimes</qex> that spurs too fast betimes.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Betitle</ent>⟦br⟧
